metas.name: Daniel Tiger's Neighborhood
metas.description: Continues the legacy of Mr. Rogers' Neighborhood with songs and lessons about social-emotional development, similar to Bluey's focus on emotional learning and Curious George's gentle exploration.

metas.name: Sesame Street
metas.description: A foundational educational show with a mix of live-action and animation, featuring beloved characters and focusing on letters, numbers, and social skills, appealing to the educational aspect of Curious George.

metas.name: Wild Kratts
metas.description: Combines animation and live-action to teach kids about animals and their habitats, offering an adventurous and educational experience similar to the curiosity explored in Curious George.

metas.name: The Magic School Bus Rides Again
metas.description: An animated educational series that takes kids on exciting scientific adventures, resonating with the learning-through-exploration theme of Curious George.

metas.name: Puffin Rock
metas.description: A gentle and beautifully animated series about two young puffins and their adventures, with a focus on nature and family bonds, reminiscent of the heartwarming feel of Bluey.

metas.name: Molly of Denali
metas.description: An animated series that follows a young girl's adventures in Alaska, incorporating Native Alaskan culture and promoting literacy and problem-solving, aligning with educational goals and gentle storytelling.

metas.name: Peg + Cat
metas.description: An animated show that teaches basic math concepts through fun and engaging stories, appealing to the educational and problem-solving aspects found in Curious George.

metas.name: Doc McStuffins
metas.description: A heartwarming animated series where a young girl can talk to her toys and fix them, promoting empathy, health awareness, and problem-solving.

metas.name: Super Wings!
metas.description: Animated series where a jet plane delivers packages to children around the world, introducing different cultures and problem-solving in an exciting, age-appropriate way.

metas.name: Tumble Leaf
metas.description: A stop-motion animated series with a focus on exploration and discovery, perfect for preschoolers who enjoy gentle learning and imaginative play, similar to the spirit of Curious George.

metas.name: If You Give a Mouse a Cookie
metas.description: An animated anthology series based on the popular children's books, featuring charming stories about friendship and problem-solving, with a playful tone.

metas.name: Yo Gabba Gabba!
metas.description: A live-action and animated show designed to entertain and educate preschoolers with music, dancing, and lessons on healthy habits and social skills.

metas.name: Ask the StoryBots
metas.description: An animated educational show where characters find answers to kids' biggest questions, presented in a fun, musical, and informative way.

metas.name: Creative Galaxy
metas.description: An animated series that encourages creativity and art exploration in young children, similar to the imaginative play seen in Bluey.

metas.name: Go Jetters
metas.description: An animated series that teaches children about geography and famous landmarks around the world through exciting missions.

metas.name: Sarah & Duck
metas.description: A gentle and imaginative stop-motion animated series about a girl and her adopted duck, focusing on everyday adventures and curiosity.

metas.name: Lost in Oz
metas.description: An animated adventure series that follows a young Dorothy and her dog Toto as they navigate the magical Land of Oz, with elements of problem-solving and friendship.

metas.name: The Octonauts
metas.description: An animated series about a team of undersea explorers who rescue sea creatures and protect the ocean, combining adventure with marine biology education.

metas.name: Clifford the Big Red Dog
metas.description: An animated series based on the beloved book character, teaching lessons about friendship, responsibility, and kindness.

metas.name: The Cat in the Hat Knows a Lot About That!
metas.description: An animated educational series where the Cat in the Hat explores scientific concepts through engaging adventures.

metas.name: Scribbles and Ink
metas.description: An animated series that follows two best friends who solve mysteries and explore the world through the power of drawing and imagination.

metas.name: Alma's Way
metas.description: An animated series that follows a confident and creative young Latina girl as she navigates life in the Bronx, focusing on family, community, and problem-solving.

metas.name: Rhyme Time Town
metas.description: An animated musical series for preschoolers that teaches the importance of words and rhyme, with a focus on problem-solving and friendship.

metas.name: Xavier Riddle and the Secret Museum
metas.description: An animated series that helps kids learn about historical figures and events by traveling back in time, offering an educational adventure.

metas.name: The Snoopy Show
metas.description: An animated series that follows Snoopy and Woodstock on their whimsical adventures, filled with humor and heartwarming moments.

metas.name: Pinky Malinky
metas.description: A CG-animated series with a mockumentary style that follows a hot dog named Pinky and his friends as they navigate life with optimism and humor.

metas.name: Geronimo Stilton
metas.description: An animated adventure series based on the popular book character, following a mouse journalist on exciting capers and explorations.

metas.name: Dinosaur Train
metas.description: An animated series that takes preschoolers on imaginative journeys to discover different dinosaurs and learn about paleontology.

metas.name: Lily's Driftwood Bay
metas.description: A charming stop-motion animated series about a young girl who collects treasures on the beach and imagines adventures with them.

metas.name: StoryBots: Answer Time
metas.description: A follow-up to Ask the StoryBots, continuing to provide fun and engaging answers to kids' questions through music and animation.

metas.name: Olaf Presents
metas.description: A short-form animated series where Olaf retells popular Disney stories in his unique and comedic way.

metas.name: Where's Waldo?
metas.description: An animated series following Waldo and his friends as they travel the globe on exciting quests, encouraging observation and problem-solving.

metas.name: Waffles + Mochi
metas.description: A live-action and animated show where two puppets explore the world to find ingredients and cook delicious dishes, promoting healthy eating and cultural exploration.

metas.name: Hilda
metas.description: An animated adventure series about a brave young girl and her magical friends, exploring a world filled with fantastical creatures and wondrous landscapes with a sense of wonder similar to Bluey's imaginative play.

metas.name: Esme & Roy
metas.description: An animated series about two monster-sitters who help human children navigate their everyday challenges, focusing on problem-solving and emotional support.
